---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Seller AI HQ, AI tools and workflows for online sellers"
  description="Curated AI tools, tested workflows, and practical guides for marketplace sellers, small ecommerce brands, and product creators."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">AI for sellers, without hype</div>
        <h1>AI tools and workflows for people who actually sell things.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          We find, test, and explain the best AI tools for marketplace sellers, small ecommerce brands,
          and product creators. Less noise, more useful stack.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn primary" href="#tools">Explore tool categories</a>
          <a class="btn secondary" href="#guides">See starter guides</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="pill">What this site is for</div>
        <ul class="clean">
          <li>Find the right AI tools for product listings, images, SEO, and content.</li>
          <li>See practical workflows instead of generic AI advice.</li>
          <li>Build a lean seller stack without wasting money on junk tools.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="stats">
          <div class="stat"><strong>3</strong><span class="mini">core categories at launch</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>10+</strong><span class="mini">starter articles planned</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>1</strong><span class="mini">clear seller-first focus</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="tools">
    <h2>Start with the core categories</h2>
    <p class="top">We are starting with the most useful areas for online sellers, then expanding into deeper comparisons and workflows.</p>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="pill">Listings</div>
        <h3>Product copy and SEO</h3>
        <p class="mini">Tools for titles, descriptions, bullet points, keyword research, and listing optimization.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="pill">Creative</div>
        <h3>Images and mockups</h3>
        <p class="mini">Tools for product visuals, lifestyle mockups, background cleanup, and creative generation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="pill">Growth</div>
        <h3>Content and marketing</h3>
        <p class="mini">Tools for short-form content, emails, social posts, and lightweight campaign ideas.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="guides">
    <h2>What is coming next</h2>
    <p class="top">The launch version is intentionally lean. We care more about useful pages than bloated directories.</p>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Best AI tools for sellers</h3>
        <p class="mini">A curated overview page that becomes the main entry point for search and social traffic.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Starter stack under a budget</h3>
        <p class="mini">Simple recommendations for sellers who want useful tools without stacking expensive subscriptions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>AI workflow guides</h3>
        <p class="mini">Step-by-step walkthroughs for listing creation, content generation, and product presentation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="stack">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="pill">Positioning</div>
      <h2>SellerAIHQ is not another generic AI directory.</h2>
      <p class="top">
        This project is being built as a focused media asset for sellers. The goal is simple, own useful search intent,
        build trust with practical recommendations, then layer monetization through affiliate links, sponsored placements,
        and eventually AI-assisted tool matching.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
